This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization of source code. Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms in neural networks is a common technique in this field. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a new neural network architecture for the task of extreme summarization. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with summarization of source code, which is a key task in software engineering. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a novel attentional neural network architecture for a specific task. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with summarization of source code, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
